If i'm driving on the Interstate it seems to be the worst,
although the problem is constant at any speed. It it is not
so much the smell I notice but rather a headache later in the
day. I drive with the windows fully open at all times now and
don't get headaches but the CO detector still shows minor
readings on average. During stop and go traffic that is when
I notice the SMELL the strongest. The smell isn't inside
the bus though, it just comes around outside the bus to
greet me at open windows.

This evening I will try the exhaust pipe extension piece I
have. I've used it before, but not since I have replaced the
